        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3874473263" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7084744219247653637">I give up. 300+ pages were more than enough to know i hated it.<br/><br/>It is a real disappointment for such a highly rated book and for one of my favorite Arabic novelists. First of all, the reason is personal; I do not particularly like legend, epic novels and long family sagas. It always feels to me that the evolution of the setting, society and time is at the account of character evolution. Second, it is that the plot was not captivating by any sense. i did not like or relate to any character. I trie</span>
  <span id="freeText7084744219247653637" style="display:none">I give up. 300+ pages were more than enough to know i hated it.<br /><br />It is a real disappointment for such a highly rated book and for one of my favorite Arabic novelists. First of all, the reason is personal; I do not particularly like legend, epic novels and long family sagas. It always feels to me that the evolution of the setting, society and time is at the account of character evolution. Second, it is that the plot was not captivating by any sense. i did not like or relate to any character. I tried to focus on symbolism, which Mahfouz is a master of, again failed to find a hook.<br /><br />One of those unpopular reviews, but i gotta be true to my self.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7084744219247653637" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

