        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer64616085" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8460923757262739503">Clan politics, corruption, and the lives of the generations of clan leaders and their families following Ashur al-Nagi.<br/><br/>Rereading to make notes....<br/><br/>I think this is my new favorite read by Mahfouz. Ten compact chapters, each possessing a rhythm as the lives of the generations are chronicled. The dervishes sing without ceasing and without every opening their gate, the night gives way to day, someone is born and dies, the only permanence is the change. <br/><br/> </span>

          </span>
        </div>


