        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2674554476" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5084106373795189281">Feels weird to review an Arabic book in English, but I feel like I wouldn&apos;t be able to give this book its fair dues otherwise. Having only recently gotten back to reading Arabic books, a thing I am woefully behind on, I am blown away by everything in this novel. The marriage of fantasy and reality, in a very specific Egyptian flavor that feels like I&apos;m being told an age-old myth. The sensation of time being cyclical, generations of the same family going through the same events - or a variation o</span>
  <span id="freeText5084106373795189281" style="display:none">Feels weird to review an Arabic book in English, but I feel like I wouldn't be able to give this book its fair dues otherwise. Having only recently gotten back to reading Arabic books, a thing I am woefully behind on, I am blown away by everything in this novel. The marriage of fantasy and reality, in a very specific Egyptian flavor that feels like I'm being told an age-old myth. The sensation of time being cyclical, generations of the same family going through the same events - or a variation of them - as they grow rich and powerful and then have their dreams crash down due to desires that almost seem inherited from father to son. Mahfouz's writing is impeccable, mixing formal and informal language in a manner that feels real, a snapshot from a time long past. Will be thinking about this masterpiece for a long time.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5084106373795189281" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


